Bonnie's just the sweetest thing.</i>

721
00:45:40,233 --> 00:45:41,276
<i>Yeah, right.</i>

722
00:45:41,401 --> 00:45:43,736
NIPPAL: <i>Celeste, she is
an accomplished attorney,</i>

723
00:45:43,820 --> 00:45:45,870
<i>and some people in this town resent that.</i>

724
00:45:46,155 --> 00:45:49,242
Rich, beautiful, madly in love.

725
00:45:50,242 --> 00:45:51,542
Something had to be wrong.

726
00:45:57,541 --> 00:45:58,834
PERRY: [SOFTLY] Hey!

727
00:46:02,004 --> 00:46:03,088
Hey.

728
00:46:03,213 --> 00:46:04,313
What are you thinking?

729
00:46:06,967 --> 00:46:09,761
I'm trying to decide
whether I'm happy or sad.

730
00:46:10,971 --> 00:46:12,430
People usually know.

731
00:46:17,393 --> 00:46:18,853
I'm sad because…

732
00:46:21,981 --> 00:46:24,692
Because my husband doubts my love for him.

733
00:46:27,111 --> 00:46:28,612
And happy?

734
00:46:30,114 --> 00:46:33,491
I'm happy because, the first
time in a long time, I'm hopeful…

735
00:46:36,244 --> 00:46:37,454
…for us.

736
00:46:44,878 --> 00:46:46,796
["HARVEST MOON" PLAYING]

737
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:55,304
Would you dance with me?

738
00:46:57,348 --> 00:47:00,642
I just want to hold
you, look into your eyes,

739
00:47:02,144 --> 00:47:03,979
be in love with you,

740
00:47:05,189 --> 00:47:07,066
and feel you being in love with me.

741
00:47:10,027 --> 00:47:11,153
Would you?

742
00:47:37,886 --> 00:47:39,638
[SOFTLY] The most beautiful song

743
00:47:41,348 --> 00:47:43,433
with the most beautiful woman.

744
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:05,037
Don't give up on me, baby.

